						               													<description>The Spanish Civil War at Sea&amp;#10;In summer of 1936 the Spanish Navy was the eighth world naval power, with 2 battleships, 4 cruisers, 15 destroyers and 12 submarines. Following the nation's fate, the Navy was also split in two. War at sea was mostly long and hard convoy warfare blockade, counter-blockade and a few naval suface actions (like the sinking of the Baleares heavy cruiser). Anyway, much like on land, both sides fought with equal valor at sea.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Mar Rojo&amp;quot; (Red Sea, The name of a merchant ship that was part of both navies) is an exciting, fast-paced card battle wargame for one or two players about the Spanish Civil War at sea.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player begins with five cards in the hand and a fleet of 12-5 ships. The object of the game is try to sink the enemy warships while the own merchant ships arrive at secure harbour.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
